com.smartsockets
Class TipcMsgEnumeratorElement

java.lang.Object
  com.smartsockets.TipcMsgEnumeratorElement
public class TipcMsgEnumeratorElement
extends java.lang.Object

This is the Object that is returned when TipcMsgEnumerator.nextElement() is invoked. This object can then be used to retrieve the appropriate field based on type. 

  TipcMsg msg = null;
  char c = 'a';
  short short_value = 10;
  TipcMsgEnumerator msgEnumerator = null;
  try {
    msg = TipcSvc.createMsg(TipcMt.INFO);
    msg.appendChar(c);
    msg.appendUnknown(TipcMsg.FT_INT4);
    msg.appendInt2(short_value);
    msg.addNamedStr("test str name", "test str value");

    msgEnumerator = msg.getEnumerator();

    TipcMsgEnumeratorElement enum_element = null;
    while(msgEnumerator.hasMoreElements()) {
      enum_element = (TipcMsgEnumeratorElement)msgEnumerator.nextElement();

      System.out.println("index = " + enum_element.getIndex());
      System.out.println("isNamed = " + enum_element.isNamed());
      if (enum_element.isNamed()) {
        System.out.println("Named field's name = " + enum_element.getName());
      }
      if (enum_element.getType() == TipcMsg.FT_CHAR) {
       System.out.println("CHAR VALUE = " + enum_element.getChar());
      }
      if (enum_element.getType() == TipcMsg.FT_INT2) {
       System.out.println("INT2 VALUE = " + enum_element.getInt2());
      }
      if (enum_element.getType() == TipcMsg.FT_STR) {
        System.out.println("STR VALUE = " + enum_element.getStr());
       }
    }
 }  catch (TipcException e) { System.out.println(e.toString()); }
